   <text type="letter">
      <body>
         <pb facs="lathrop01.jpg" xml:id="pb0001" n="1"/>
         <head type="metadata">
             <name corresp="#JPL">George Parsons Lathrop</name> to <addressee>
               <name corresp="#SLC">Samuel L. Clemens</name>
            </addressee>
             <date when="1884-03-29">29 March 1884</date> &#x2022; <placeName>New York, New York</placeName>
            <sourceline>(MS: CU-MARK, UCLC 41840)</sourceline>
         </head>
         <div1 type="letter" xml:id="lt0001">
            <opener>
               <dateline rend="indentdateline"><address>80 Washington Sq.<space extent="3"/>
                   <addrLine><placeName>New York<space extent="2"/></placeName></addrLine></address>
                  <date when="1884-03-29">Mar 29/84.</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>Dear Mr. Clemens,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p rend="text-indent:2">As a faithful reader of as many of your productions as I have been able to get track of or keep up with, I am desirous of securing your autograph, to add to my own, &amp; to the autographs of other distinguished persons.</p>
            <p rend="text-indent:2">May I hope that you will confer upon me the favor of writing out neatly upon a large sheet of paper <pb facs="lathrop02.jpg" xml:id="pb0002" n="2"/>your favorite sentiments &amp; beliefs, carefully selected from your various works, with your signature appended?
            </p>
            <p rend="text-indent:2">Should you not have time to do this, an original unpublished composition would be received with gratitude.
            </p>
            <closer rend="indentcompclose">
                <salute rend="indentcompclose">Respectfully yours,</salute>
               <signed rend="indentsig">G. P. Lathrop.</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p><label>P.S.</label> Stamps will be sent you, on receipt of MS.</p>
            </postscript>
         </div1>
